parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear on Brake Pads and Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads and rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents, and requiring frequent replacements, which can be costly and inconvenient.
symptoms: Frequent need to replace brake pads and rotors
uneven wear on brake pads and rotors
reduced braking performance
squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS braking system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes lock up
rear brakes do not activate
brakes malfunction on transition from gravel to smooth road
brakes malfunction when applied after driving on gravel roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake lock-up in wet conditions can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes lock up when driving in rain
brakes malfunction in wet conditions
reduced braking performance in wet conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to restrain the driver or passenger properly can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to hold the driver or passenger in place
the seat belt shoulder harness gives out
the seat belt buckle is difficult to unbuckle
the driver or passenger is able to hit their head on the steering wheel or other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose vital information about the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is blank or dim
the speedometer
fuel gauge
oil gauge
and/or battery gauge are not functioning
the gauges are stuck or frozen
the display is distorted or flickering.
